# RFC v0.2 Revision Spec — Final

## Governing Principle

One governance vote. Two delivery-gated tranches. Public infrastructure grant-funded. Commercial operations out of scope.

**Lead with what's built, fund what's defensible, gate what's speculative.**

## Phase 1 — Open Transparency Layer ($120K, months 1–6)

**Deliverables:**
- DIG/YTD deployed against top 30 Morpho vaults by TVL
- DIG/YTD public release (when documentation-ready, not forced pre-vote)
- Structured monitoring: oracle staleness alerts, governance mutation detection, leverage loop flagging
- Vault dossiers with dependency graphs, qualitative risk findings labeled as analyst assessment
- Dashboard v1
- Retroactive case studies with "designed to detect" framing
- 2 named curator trials initiated

**Tranche 1 gate (all objective):**
- All Phase 1 deliverables verified
- 2 named curator trials live or completed
- DIG/YTD code publicly available

## Phase 2 — Quantitative Scoring Layer ($130K, months 7–12)

**Deliverables:**
- Z1-Z6 factor scoring, GJR-GARCH-t calibration, HMM regime-switching
- Effective volatility, intrinsic rating (AAA-CCC), contextual PD (1d/7d/30d)
- All outputs in shadow mode minimum 60 days, published, non-binding
- External methodology review completed
- 50+ assets covered
- Full open-source release of scoring layer

**Tranche 2 gate (all objective):**
- Phase 1 milestones verified
- 30+ days of public shadow-mode outputs running
- External methodology reviewer engaged or review completed
- At least one curator trial has produced written evaluation

## Budget

| Category | Phase 1 | Phase 2 | Total |
|---|---|---|---|
| Personnel (2.5 FTE) | $75K | $75K | $150K |
| Infrastructure | $10K | $10K | $20K |
| External methodology review | - | $35K | $35K |
| Frontend / dashboard | $25K | $10K | $35K |
| Legal / ops | $10K | - | $10K |
| **Total** | **$120K** | **$130K** | **$250K** |

Footnote: Team members have independent income sources. Grant rates are below market. This makes the project feasible at $250K; it also constrains execution bandwidth, which is why Phase 1 and Phase 2 are separated.

## Section Revisions

- **Abstract:** Lead with wsrUSD yield tree artifact, then DIG/YTD as operational, then incidents as "what was readable on-chain," then gap statement, then two-phase summary
- **Motivation:** One paragraph Chaos Labs (both edges). Prosperi 20-100x mispricing. LucaB quant cost. Name the public goods problem explicitly
- **Credora:** Direct answer. Different architectural layer. Reference wstETH CAPO incident. "Open structural infrastructure any framework can consume as input"
- **Development:** Two milestone tables. Label wsrUSD scorecard as analyst assessment
- **Budget:** Personnel/non-personnel split
- **Team:** Lead with role and contribution, not school names. Add curator trial commitments
- **Post-Grant Sustainability (new):** Maintenance framing. Exit clause: community handover if $150K ARR not reached in 18 months. Drop insurance pricing
- **Evidence Appendix E3:** Honest header. Replace "would have flagged" with "is designed to detect"
- **Technical Appendix:** No changes

## Pre-Submission Checklist

**Blocking (resolve before any writing):**
1. What Morpho governance wants to fund — Daniel
2. 2 named curator trial commitments — Daniel
3. DIG/YTD code readiness assessment — Daniel + team
4. 2-3 candidate methodology reviewers shortlisted — Amaury + Hamza

**Writing (parallelize after 1-4 have answers):**
5. Integrate Chaos Labs, Prosperi, LucaB into Motivation
6. Restructure budget
7. Rewrite Abstract (artifact-first)
8. Rewrite Credora section
9. Add sustainability section with exit clause
10. Downgrade E3 retroactive claims

## Out of Scope for the RFC

- Commercial pricing, subscription tiers, SaaS revenue projections
- Curator scoring or ranking
- Insurance pricing
- Multi-chain expansion
- Full smart contract audit
- Any claim the model "would have prevented" past incidents

