# RFC v0.2 Revision Spec — Final

## Governing principle
- One governance vote, two delivery-gated tranches
- Grant covers public infrastructure only
- Commercial operations are explicitly out of scope
- Positioning: lead with what is built, fund what is defensible, gate what is speculative

## Phase 1 — Open Transparency Layer ($120K, months 1–6)
- Deploy DIG/YTD against the top 30 Morpho vaults by TVL
- Publicly release DIG/YTD when documentation and packaging are ready
- Ship structured monitoring for oracle staleness, governance mutations, and leverage-loop detection
- Publish vault dossiers with dependency graphs and qualitative findings clearly labeled as analyst assessment
- Ship dashboard v1
- Publish retroactive case studies using “designed to detect” / “readable on-chain” framing
- Start 2 named curator trials

### Tranche 1 gate
- All Phase 1 deliverables verified
- 2 named curator trials live or completed
- DIG/YTD code publicly available

## Phase 2 — Quantitative Scoring Layer ($130K, months 7–12)
- Build Z1–Z6 factor scoring
- Complete GJR-GARCH-t calibration and HMM regime-switching
- Publish effective volatility, intrinsic rating (AAA–CCC), and contextual PD (1d/7d/30d)
- Run all scoring outputs in public non-binding shadow mode for at least 60 days
- Complete external methodology review
- Cover 50+ assets
- Open-source the scoring layer

### Tranche 2 gate
- Phase 1 milestones verified
- 30+ days of public shadow-mode outputs running
- External methodology reviewer engaged or review completed
- At least one curator trial has produced a written evaluation

## Budget
| Category | Phase 1 | Phase 2 | Total |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| Personnel (2.5 FTE) | $75K | $75K | $150K |
| Infrastructure | $10K | $10K | $20K |
| External methodology review | - | $35K | $35K |
| Frontend / dashboard | $25K | $10K | $35K |
| Legal / ops | $10K | - | $10K |
| **Total** | **$120K** | **$130K** | **$250K** |

- Footnote: team members have independent income sources; grant rates are below market; that makes the project feasible at this budget and is why execution is split into two phases

## Required section changes
- Abstract: artifact-first; open with wsrUSD yield tree, then DIG/YTD, then incidents as readable on-chain, then gap, then two-phase ask
- Motivation: add Chaos Labs, Prosperi, and LucaB; explicitly name the public-goods problem
- Credora: answer directly; different architectural layer; open structural infrastructure any framework can consume
- Development: split into Phase 1 and Phase 2 milestone tables
- Budget: switch to personnel vs non-personnel presentation
